==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Majuscule
<hw>Ma*jus"cule</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>majuscule</ets>. See <er>Majusculae</er>.]</ety> <def>A capital
letter; especially, one used in ancient manuscripts. See
<er>Majusculae</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Majuscule writing</b></col>, <cd>writing composed wholly
of capital letters, especially the style which prevailed in Europe from
the third to the sixth century.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>makable</ent>⟦br⟧
